broadcast:  Simple Broadcasted Binding and Binary Operations for Atomic and Recursive Arrays with Minimal Dependencies.   Implements simple broadcasted operations for atomic and recursive arrays.
Besides linking to ‚ÄòRcpp‚Äô, ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô does not depend on, vendor, link to, include, or otherwise use any external libraries; ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô was essentially made from scratch and can be installed out-of-the-box.
The broadcasted implementations include, but are not limited to, the following:


A more efficient and broadcasted version of abind(), for binding arrays along an arbitrary dimension;


Relational operations (like ==, !=, &lt;, &gt;, &lt;=, &gt;=; can also take into account Machine precision);


Arithmetic operations (like +, -, *, /, "gcd", ^, pmin(), pmax());


Boolean combiner operations (like &, |, xor(), "nand");


String distance, (in)equality, and concatenation operations;


A Broadcasted implementation of ifelse();


A Broadcasted apply-like function; The broadcasted implementations strive to minimize computation time and memory usage (which is not just good for computer efficiency, but also for the environment).





An introduction and overview of the package can be found on the website.  



Outer-like functions  ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô provides a set of functions for binary, element-wise, outer operations with broadcasting.  These functions use an API similar to the outer and sweep functions.   The following functions for type-specific binary operations are available:


bc.b: Boolean operations;


bc.i: integer (53bit) arithmetic and relational operations;


bc.d: decimal (64bit) arithmetic and relational operations;


bc.cplx: complex arithmetic and (in)equality operations;


bc.str: string (in)equality, concatenation, and distance operations;


bc.list: apply any ‚ÄòR‚Äô function to 2 recursive arrays with broadcasting.  


Binding Implementations  ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô provides 3 binding implementations:  bind_mat, bind_array, and bind_dt.  
General functions  ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô also comes with 2 general broadcasted functions:


bc_ifelse: Broadcasted version of ifelse.


bcapply: Broadcasted apply-like function.  


Other functions  ‚Äòbroadcast‚Äô also provides type-casting functions, which preserve names and dimensions - convenient for arrays.  



Author, Maintainer: Tony Wilkes tony_a_wilkes@outlook.com (ORCID)



The badges shown in the documentation of this R-package were made using the services of: https://shields.io/

